{"type":"message","id":"a2c17b8d","parentId":"8fa0f642","timestamp":"2026-05-20T12:04:07.267Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to add a rule: the person who requested the story should be set as the handler (owner) of the parent story. So if Yousan asks me to create a story, Yousan should be the owner. If 兵王 asks, 兵王 should be the owner.\n\nI need to check who the sender is. Looking at the conversation info:\n- sender_id: ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f\n- sender: Yousan(叶枝君)\n- name: Yousan(叶枝君)\n\nSo the sender is 叶枝君. The parent story's handler should be 叶枝君.\n\nCurrently the script doesn't set the parent story's owner at all. I need to add this.\n\nBut wait - I need to think about how to determine who the requester is. In the script, I need to accept a `handler` parameter for the parent story. When called from the CLI, the requester is implicit.\n\nLet me think about this:\n1. When the user says \"提个需求单\" in a message, I know who the sender is from the inbound context\n2. I need to pass this info to the script\n\nThe simplest approach: add a `handler` CLI argument to the script. When called from the main session, I pass the sender's name.\n\nLet me update create_story.mjs to:\n1. Accept a `handler` option (default empty, meaning no handler set)\n2. Fill in the `data[Story][owner]` field with the handler name\n3. Also fill in the autocomplete field\n\nActually, looking at the current script, it fills in fields in the page and then submits via fetch. But it doesn't fill in the owner field. I need to add that.\n\nFor the parent story owner, I can just add `fd.set('data[Story][owner]', handler)` to the form data.\n\nLet me update the skill and script.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"明白，母单处理人 = 发单人。我来更新脚本。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_YW6AlkVJXloaGmTNTd8a3738","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\create_story.mjs","offse