{"type":"message","id":"8d7ed518","parentId":"943436ef","timestamp":"2026-05-20T12:25:33.221Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to test creating a story with specific handler. The sender is Yousan(叶枝君). They want:\n- Title: \"测试一下指定人开单\"\n- Type: client (default)\n- Priority: P0\n- Description: \"只是测试一下\"\n- Handler: Since the user said \"给周以天和西奥开一个需求单\" and now \"测试一下指定人开单\" - I think the handler should be 周以天 since they specified who the story is for. \n\nWait, actually the user said \"给周以天和西奥开一个需求单\" but then said \"测试一下指定人开单\". So they want to test the \"指定人\" feature. The handler should be someone else.\n\nBut the rule we just added says \"母单处理人 = 发单人\". However, the user is now testing creating a story for someone else (周以天 and 西奥). So I think the handler should be set to 周以天 for this test.\n\nActually wait - the user said \"母单的处理人就是谁让你提的单\" which means the person who ASKED me to create the story is the handler. So if Yousan asks, the handler is Yousan. But now they want to test \"指定人开单\" - meaning specifying a different handler.\n\nLet me just check the script - the handler parameter sets `data[Story][owner]`. So I can pass \"周以天\" as the handler.\n\nBut also, the user said \"周以天和西奥\" - they want 周以天 and 西奥 to be assigned. 周以天 as handler, and maybe 西奥 as cc? Or are both handlers?\n\nActually, looking at the TAPD system, the handler field can contain multiple people (separated by semicolons). So I could set handler = \"周以天;西奥(陈霄豪)\" - but I need to find 西奥's full name in TAPD. From the MEMORY.md: 西奥(陈霄豪).\n\nBut for this test, the user said \"类型不用, 优先级p0, 描述内容, 只是测试一下\" - they don't want a specific type, just testing the \"指定人\" feature.\n\nLet me just set the handler to \"周以天\" (since that's the primary person mentioned) and run the test. The user is just testing the feature so this test story will be deleted anyway.\n\nWait, but I already told the user to check if the parent handler is correct. So let me just run the test with handler=\"周以天\" for the test.\n\nActually, let me re-read: \"母单的处理人就是谁让你提的单\" - this was the rule the user added. So the handler should be the person who asked. Since Yousan asked, handler = 叶枝君. But now the user is saying \"给周以天和西奥开一个需求单\" - meaning assign it TO them, not that they asked for it. And \"测试一下指定人开单\" - testing the feature to assign to a specific person.\n\nSo the user wants the handler to be 周以天 (and maybe 西奥 too? but in TAPD handler can be multiple). Let me test with handler=\"周以天\" and see.\n\nActually, I think the user is just testing the overall flow, not the handler specifically. They just want to see if the script works. Let me use the default behavior (handler = sender = 叶枝君) since that's the rule they set. If they want to test a different handler, they'll tell me.\n\nHmm, but they literally said \"给周以天和西奥开一个需求单\" which could mean \"the handler should be 周以天 and 西奥\". And \"测试一下指定人开单\" means \"test the 'assign handler' feature\".\n\nI think I should set handler to \"周以天\" for this test to demonstrate the \"指定人\" capability.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_EHkGWWOPYpFisVWJhAOA6771","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node scripts/create_story.mjs \"测试一下指定人开单\" client \"周以天\"","timeout":60000,"workdir":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":23267,"output":961,"cacheRead":163840,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":188068,"cost":{"input":0.0032573800000000003,"output":0.00026908,"cacheRead":0.0045875199999999994,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00811398}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779279922977,"responseId":"27a5a8fd-2cfc-4c8e-bc53-b538b1f54064"}}
