{"type":"message","id":"05bf2e00","parentId":"14c7ddc0","timestamp":"2026-05-20T12:58:53.746Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the members page loads successfully. The members list is visible, but the roles column wasn't captured. Let me look at the screenshot to understand the layout better. \n\nAlso the Node.js API call returned 200 but there was no output - it seems the script exited before printing the members from the API call.\n\nLet me check the screenshot to understand the member management page structure.\n\nBut actually, I have enough info now:\n1. GitLab instance: git.devcloud.ztgame.com\n2. Authenticated as yezhijun (叶枝君)\n3. Can access API with cookie\n4. Member management is at `/-/project_members` under each project\n5. GitLab API v4 available\n\nLet me try the API calls again with a cleaner approach to test adding members, and also look at the screenshot.\n\nActually, let me look at the screenshot first.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_5DnNjCc8FJcMLOkkmFwg4075","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\media\\gitlab_members.png"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":396,"output":248,"cacheRead":215040,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":215684,"cost":{"input":0.000055440000000000005,"output":0.00006944,"cacheRead":0.00602112,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0061459999999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779281930294,"responseId":"810ab269-20bd-4223-8778-32438c8a29f4"}}
