{"type":"message","id":"938151a1","parentId":"8b4ec12e","timestamp":"2026-05-20T13:25:16.117Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, `line.length` gives the JS string length (not visual width). The dash line using `line.length - 2` might not account for Chinese chars properly. Let me think...\n\nActually, the dashes `-` are ASCII, so `'-'.repeat(line.length - 2)` will create ASCII dashes. But line.length counts Chinese chars as 1, when they display as 2 cells wide. So the dash line would be too short if there are Chinese chars in the header.\n\nHmm, this is getting complex. Let me just use a simpler approach: calculate the visual width of the entire header line and generate dashes based on that.\n\nActually, let me just calculate the total visual width and use that.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_NLUA6n8cwRE1KnZlAY583287","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\log_operation.mjs","edits":[{"oldText":"  console.log(`\\n最近 ${recent.length} 条日志：`);\n  const sep = ' | ';\n  const line = '| ' + pad('人', nw) + sep + pad('事情', tw) + sep + pad('结果', rw) + ' |';\n  const dash = '|' + '-' .repeat(line.length - 2) + '|';\n  console.log(line);\n  console.log(dash);\n  recent.forEach(l => {\n    console.log('| ' + pad(l.sender, nw) + sep + pad(l.type, tw) + sep + pad(l.result, rw) + ' |');\n  });","newText":"  console.log(`\\n最近 ${recent.length} 条日志：`);\n  // 计算表头+分隔线宽度\n  const twTotal = 4 + nw + 4 + tw + 4 + rw + 3; // | 人 + pad | 事情 + pad | 结果 + pad |\n  console.log('| ' + pad('人', nw) + ' | ' + pad('事情', tw) + ' | ' + pad('结果', rw) + ' |');\n  console.log('|' + '-'.repeat(nw + 2) + '|' + '-'.repeat(tw + 2) + '|' + '-'.repeat(rw + 2) + '|');\n  recent.forEach(l => {\n    console.log('| ' + pad(l.sender, nw) + ' | ' + pad(l.type, tw) + ' | ' + pad(l.result, rw) + ' |');\n  });"}]}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepse