{"type":"message","id":"ca2e0c55","parentId":"13f64b3b","timestamp":"2026-05-20T13:25:23.373Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now the issue is that nw and rw are visual widths (Chinese = 2, ASCII = 1). The dash line uses `'-'.repeat(nw + 2)` which creates ASCII dashes. But when displayed, the Chinese chars in the data rows take up 2 cells each, but the dashes are only 1 cell each. So the dash line would be shorter than the data lines.\n\nThe correct approach: convert visual widths to \"JS string character count\" for the dash line. Since I'm padding with spaces (which are 1 cell wide), and the data itself has mixed widths, the total visual width of each cell is: pad + spacing. But the dashes `-` are always 1 cell wide, so `'-'.repeat(nw + 2)` creates `nw+2` dashes which display as `nw+2` cells. And the cell visual width should be `nw + 2` too.\n\nWait, let me trace:\n- Cell: `| ` + pad(sender, nw) + ` |`\n- visual width of `| ` = 2\n- visual width of pad(sender, nw): sender visual width + padding spaces = nw\n- visual width of ` |` = 2\n- Total cell visual width = 2 + nw + 2 = nw + 4\n\nDash: `|` + `-`.repeat(nw+2) + `|`\n- visual width = 1 + (nw+2) + 1 = nw + 4\n\nThese should match! Because:\n- Cell: | + space + (sender + spaces of visual width nw) + space + | = 1+1+nw+1+1 = nw+4\n- Dash: | + nw+2 dashes + | = 1+(nw+2)+1 = nw+4\n\nYes, this should work correctly! Let me test.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_z2l6y9pX0OwTof5xIlFl2384","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node scripts/log_operation.mjs \"测试\" \"杨罗平\" \"开权限\" \"成功\"","timeout":5000,"workdir":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":65,"output":527,"cacheRead":253824,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":254416,"cost":{"input":0.000009100000000000001,"output":0.00014756,"cacheRead":0.007107072,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.007263732