{"type":"message","id":"b4067807","parentId":"1ff088f3","timestamp":"2026-05-20T13:25:30.956Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, there seems to be a visual issue. Let me look at the header line:\n```\n| 人     | 事情       | 结果 |\n```\n\n\"人\" is 2 visual width, padded to nw which is max sender width. Let me check: \"杨罗平\" = 6 width, \"Yousan(叶枝君)\" = 16 width. So nw = 16.\n\n\"人\" + pad(\"人\", 16) = \"人\" + 14 spaces = 16 visual width.\n\nBut the displayed line shows \"| 人     |\" - that's \"人\" plus about 5 spaces = 7 visual width. That doesn't look right.\n\nOh wait - the recent logs from the test run don't include \"Yousan(叶枝君)\" since I just changed the script and re-ran. The current logs have shorter names: 杨罗平(6), 兵王(4), 谭佳钦(6). So nw = 6.\n\n\"人\" has visLen=2, needs to pad to 6. So \"人\" + 4 spaces = \"人    \" (6 visual cells). Then \" | \" separator. That should give \"| 人     |\" which is \"人\" + 4spaces = 6 total + 2 for \"| \" = 8 chars before the first \"|\".\n\nThe displayed output looks correct for the current data. The issue was my mental calculation was wrong. Let me just verify it looks good:\n\n```\n| 人     | 事情       | 结果 |\n|--------|------------|------|\n| 杨罗平 | 测试       | 成功 |\n```\n\n\"人\" aligned with \"杨罗平\" - the first \"|\" chars are at the same position for header and data. \"事情\" aligned with \"测试\". \"结果\" aligned with \"成功\". \n\nThis looks clean! Let me confirm with the user.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"这样呢？标准的表格格式：\n\n```\n| 人     | 事情       | 结果 |\n|--------|------------|------|\n| 杨罗平 | 测试       | 成功 |\n| 兵王   | 更新测试服 | 成功 |\n| 谭佳钦 | 提单       | 成功 |\n```"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":189,"output":480,"cacheRead":254336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":255005,"cost":{"input":0.00002646,"output":0.00013440000000000001,"cacheRead":0.007121408,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.007282268}},"stopReason":"st