{"type":"message","id":"17b42d65","parentId":"468d67b8","timestamp":"2026-05-20T13:25:59.449Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants an Excel-like table with borders. I need to use box-drawing characters (┌ ─ ┐ │ ├ ┤ └ ┴ ┘ etc.) But the issue is that box-drawing characters like `─` have different widths in different terminals - some render them as 1 cell, some as 2 cells.\n\nA simpler approach: use `+` and `-` and `|` to create a bordered table. Like:\n\n```\n+--------+------------+------+\n| 人     | 事情       | 结果 |\n+--------+------------+------+\n| 杨罗平 | 测试       | 成功 |\n| 兵王   | 更新测试服 | 成功 |\n+--------+------------+------+\n```\n\nThis is the classic ASCII table format that looks like Excel borders. Let me update the script.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_FXcl4njHFVCH0rdtJeC21368","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\log_operation.mjs","edits":[{"oldText":"  console.log(`\\n最近 ${recent.length} 条日志：`);\n  // 计算表头+分隔线宽度\n  const twTotal = 4 + nw + 4 + tw + 4 + rw + 3; // | 人 + pad | 事情 + pad | 结果 + pad |\n  console.log('| ' + pad('人', nw) + ' | ' + pad('事情', tw) + ' | ' + pad('结果', rw) + ' |');\n  console.log('|' + '-'.repeat(nw + 2) + '|' + '-'.repeat(tw + 2) + '|' + '-'.repeat(rw + 2) + '|');\n  recent.forEach(l => {\n    console.log('| ' + pad(l.sender, nw) + ' | ' + pad(l.type, tw) + ' | ' + pad(l.result, rw) + ' |');\n  });","newText":"  const top    = '+' + '-' .repeat(nw + 2) + '+' + '-' .repeat(tw + 2) + '+' + '-' .repeat(rw + 2) + '+';\n  const mid    = '+' + '-' .repeat(nw + 2) + '+' + '-' .repeat(tw + 2) + '+' + '-' .repeat(rw + 2) + '+';\n  const bottom = '+' + '-' .repeat(nw + 2) + '+' + '-' .repeat(tw + 2) + '+' + '-' .repeat(rw + 2) + '+';\n\n  console.log(`\\n最近 ${recent.length} 条日志：`);\n  console.log(top);\n  console.log('| ' + pad('人', nw) + ' | ' + pad('事情', tw) + ' | ' + pad('结果', rw) + ' |');\n  consol