{"type":"message","id":"4f57c2f2","parentId":"1594c4f0","timestamp":"2026-05-20T13:26:46.251Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user replied to an \"Interactive Card\" message, referencing some kind of card format. They want the log output to be displayed as an interactive card in Feishu, not as plain text ASCII table.\n\nIn Feishu, an interactive card is a rich message format that can include tables, buttons, etc. This is done via the Feishu message API using card JSON format.\n\nHowever, since the log_operation.mjs is a CLI script that outputs to console, and I'm relaying the info as a text message in Feishu, I need a different approach:\n\nOption A: Use the Feishu message API to send a card instead of plain text\nOption B: Use the `feishu_send_group.mjs` script pattern to send a card message\nOption C: Format the output as a readable card-like format in my response\n\nActually, I think the user wants me to send the operation log as a Feishu interactive card (rich text/card) instead of plain text. The `feishu_send_group.mjs` script sends group messages. Maybe I need to extend it or use the Feishu API to send interactive cards.\n\nBut wait - the log_operation.mjs runs from the console. It can't easily send Feishu cards from there. The user might be referring to how I display the log in my response to them (in the Feishu chat).\n\nLet me re-read: the user replied to an \"[Interactive Card]\" message. They want this style. So when I report back with the log, I should format it as a Feishu interactive card.\n\nOpenClaw has feishu skills available. Let me check if there's a way to send interactive cards.\n\nActually, the simplest approach: change the output format to be a clean markdown table with proper alignment that I can display in my response. Or I can use the feishu message sending capability.\n\nLet me check what \"[Interactive Card]\" looks like in Feishu. In Feishu, interactive cards are JSON-based rich messages that support tables, headers, buttons, etc.\n\nI think the cleanest approach is to just format the log nicely in my reply. But the user specifically wants it as a card style.\n\nActually, looking at the existing scripts, I have `feishu_send_group.mjs` which sends messages to groups. I could create a similar script that sends interactive cards with tables.\n\nBut this is getting complex. Let me first understand what format the user wants by looking at the interactive card they referenced. The reply target shows \"[Interactive Card]\" which is likely a Feishu message card with a table inside it.\n\nLet me just try a simpler approach - present the data as a clean Feishu-style card format in my replies. Or better yet, let me ask the user if they want me to integrate the log display into the Feishu card format using the existing feishu_send infrastructure.\n\nActually, I think the simplest solution: change the log output to use markdown table format in my response. The log_operation.mjs script outputs whatever format, and then I relay it. Let me just make the markdown table cleaner in my replies.\n\nWait, but the user said \"这种样式\" replying to an Interactive Card. They want the log to be displayed as a Feishu interactive card with a table. Let me check the available feishu skills to see if there's a way to send cards.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"明白，你想要飞书互动卡片（Interactive Card）那种样式。我看看能不能用飞书消息 API 发送卡片格式。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_tWpoSaiEuiwVODe84d2m3166","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\feishu_send_group.mjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":5392,"output":808,"cacheRead":251648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":257848,"cost":{"input":0.0007548800000000001,"output":0.00022624,"cacheRead":0.007046144,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008027264}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779283594951,"responseId":"f27e47a1-b577-4238-84